{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RNj6eL3DTgyVYnriNr5HH1","type":"tool_result","content":"60\t- `services/backend/src/routes/` ‚Äî existing route patterns\n61\t- `services/backend/migrations/` ‚Äî migration files (see Developer Reference below)\n62\t- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/` ‚Äî mock profile system + components\n63\t\n64\t## Contract Files\n65\t\n66\t- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/types.ts` ‚Äî `ProfileTransaction` type (frontend shape)\n67\t- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/components/ProfileTransactions.tsx` ‚Äî table component to wire\n68\t\n69\t---\n70\t\n71\t## Functional Requirements\n72\t\n73\t### FR-1: `user_transactions` Ledger Table\n74\t\n75\tA new PostgreSQL table that stores one row per user-visible game event.\n76\t\n77\t**Schema:**\n78\t\n79\t| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |\n80\t|--------|------|-------------|-------|\n81\t| `id` | `BIGSERIAL` | PK | Auto-increment |\n82\t| `wallet` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | Player wallet address |\n83\t| `game` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | `coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall` |\n84\t| `match_id` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | Links to rounds/closecall_rounds |\n85\t| `event` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | `join`, `win`, `loss`, `refund` |\n86\t| `amount_lamports` | `BIGINT` | NOT NULL | Wager (join) or payout (win) or refund amount |\n87\t| `tx_sig` | `TEXT` | | On-chain transaction signature (nullable until confirmed) |\n88\t| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | NOT NULL DEFAULT now() | Event timestamp |\n89\t\n90\t**Indexes:**\n91\t- `idx_user_tx_wallet_created` on `(wallet, created_at DESC)` ‚Äî paginated history\n92\t- `idx_user_tx_match_id` on `(match_id)` ‚Äî dedup / lookup\n93\t\n94\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n95\t- [x] Migration `007_user_transactions.sql` creates the table and indexes <!-- satisfied: migrations/008_user_transactions.sql:1-30 (named 008 because 007 was taken) ‚Äî table, 2 indexes, UNIQUE constraint -->\n96\t- [x] Migration runs cleanly on a fresh DB and on an existing DB <!-- satisfied: standard IF NOT EXISTS DDL pattern; confirmed in history iterations 1 + 11 -->\n97\t- [x] No backfill of historical data (table starts empty) <!-- satisfied: migrations/008_user_transactions.sql contains only DDL, no INSERT/UPDATE -->\n98\t\n99\t### FR-2: Write Path ‚Äî Populate on Settlement\n100\t\n101\tThe settlement worker writes to `user_transactions` when a round settles.\n102\tAll writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` on `(wallet, match_id, event)` for\n103\tidempotency.\n104\t\n105\t**Coinflip** (commit-reveal, 1v1):\n106\t- **Join ‚Äî creator**: Written when the create route inserts the round into DB\n107\t  (creator wallet is known at create time).\n108\t- **Join ‚Äî opponent**: Written when PDA watcher detects phase change to LOCKED\n109\t  (opponent wallet readable from on-chain account).\n110\t- **Win + Loss**: On `settle_confirmed` in `settle-tx.ts`, insert two rows.\n111\t  `win.amount_lamports` = payout (after fees). `loss.amount_lamports` =\n112\t  original wager.\n113\t\n114\t**Lord of the RNGs** (commit-reveal, multi-player):\n115\t- **No join rows** ‚Äî the PDA watcher sees the round state change but not\n116\t  individual entries. Join visibility is deferred.\n117\t- **Win + Loss**: On `settle_confirmed` in `settle-tx.ts`, insert one `win`\n118\t  row for the winner and one `loss` row per losing entry. Entries array is\n119\t  available from on-chain round data at settlement time.\n120\t\n121\t**Close Call** (pari-mutuel):\n122\t- **All rows at settlement**: When `settleRound()` in `closecall-clock.ts`\n123\t  completes, write one `join` + one outcome (`win`/`loss`/`refund`) row per\n124\t  entry. Entries are in the round's `green_entries`/`red_entries` JSONB.\n125\t- **Refund rows**: Only Close Call has backend-processed refunds (one-sided\n126\t  rounds, single player, equal price). Coinflip/Lord refunds are\n127\t  permissionless on-chain timeout ‚Äî the backend doesn't process them.\n128\t\n129\t**Game name mapping**: DB stores `coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall`. API maps to\n130\tfrontend `GameId`: `lord` ‚Üí `lord-of-rngs`, `closecall` ‚Üí `close-call`.\n131\t\n132\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n133\t- [x] Coinflip: creator join row written at create time <!-- satisfied: routes/create.ts:208-215 ‚Äî insertUserTransaction after round INSERT -->\n134\t- [x] Coinflip: opponent join row written at PDA watcher lock detection <!-- satisfied: worker/pda-watcher.ts:120-132 ‚Äî fire-and-forget on PHASE_LOCKED -->\n135\t- [x] Coinflip: win + loss rows written at settlement with correct amounts and tx_sig <!-- satisfied: worker/settle-tx.ts:304-323 ‚Äî Promise.all win(payoutAmount)+loss(entryAmount) with txSignature -->\n136\t- [x] Lord: win row for winner + loss rows for all losers at settlement <!-- satisfied: worker/settle-tx.ts:518-543 ‚Äî win(payoutAmount) + loss per non-winner entry -->\n137\t- [x] Close Call: join + outcome rows per entry at settlement <!-- satisfied: worker/closecall-clock.ts:489-538 ‚Äî iterates green/red entries, join+outcome per entry -->\n138\t- [x] Close Call: refund rows written for refund outcomes <!-- satisfied: worker/closecall-clock.ts:508-509,523-524 ‚Äî isRefund check writes refund event -->\n139\t- [x] `match_id` links back to the correct round in `rounds` or `closecall_rounds` <!-- satisfied: coinflip/lord use round.match_id‚Üírounds; closecall uses roundId‚Üíclosecall_rounds.round_id -->\n140\t- [x] No duplicate rows for the same event (idempotent via ON CONFLICT) <!-- satisfied: UNIQUE(wallet,match_id,event) in migration:27-29; all paths use ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING -->\n141\t\n142\t### FR-3: API Endpoint ‚Äî Transaction History\n143\t\n144\t```\n145\tGET /profile/transactions?cursor=<id>&limit=<n>&game=<filter>\n146\t```\n147\t\n148\t- **Auth**: JWT required. Returns transactions only for the authenticated\n149\t  wallet (from JWT `sub` claim). No wallet parameter in URL ‚Äî prevents\n150\t  enumeration.\n151\t- **Pagination**: Cursor-based using `id` (descending). Default limit 20,\n152\t  max 50.\n153\t- **Filtering**: Optional `game` query param (`coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall`).\n154\t- **Response shape**:\n155\t  ```json\n156\t  {\n157\t    \"transactions\": [\n158\t      {\n159\t        \"id\": 123,"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"056dd687-a09d-4a16-94d1-459ad839de8f","uuid":"1af13bcb-8744-4bc2-8752-29e2e78aa071","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:22:49.186Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/008-user-profile/spec.md","content":"- `services/backend/src/routes/` ‚Äî existing route patterns\n- `services/backend/migrations/` ‚Äî migration files (see Developer Reference below)\n- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/` ‚Äî mock profile system + components\n\n## Contract Files\n\n- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/types.ts` ‚Äî `ProfileTransaction` type (frontend shape)\n- `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/components/ProfileTransactions.tsx` ‚Äî table component to wire\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: `user_transactions` Ledger Table\n\nA new PostgreSQL table that stores one row per user-visible game event.\n\n**Schema:**\n\n| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------------|-------|\n| `id` | `BIGSERIAL` | PK | Auto-increment |\n| `wallet` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | Player wallet address |\n| `game` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | `coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall` |\n| `match_id` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | Links to rounds/closecall_rounds |\n| `event` | `TEXT` | NOT NULL | `join`, `win`, `loss`, `refund` |\n| `amount_lamports` | `BIGINT` | NOT NULL | Wager (join) or payout (win) or refund amount |\n| `tx_sig` | `TEXT` | | On-chain transaction signature (nullable until confirmed) |\n| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ` | NOT NULL DEFAULT now() | Event timestamp |\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `idx_user_tx_wallet_created` on `(wallet, created_at DESC)` ‚Äî paginated history\n- `idx_user_tx_match_id` on `(match_id)` ‚Äî dedup / lookup\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Migration `007_user_transactions.sql` creates the table and indexes <!-- satisfied: migrations/008_user_transactions.sql:1-30 (named 008 because 007 was taken) ‚Äî table, 2 indexes, UNIQUE constraint -->\n- [x] Migration runs cleanly on a fresh DB and on an existing DB <!-- satisfied: standard IF NOT EXISTS DDL pattern; confirmed in history iterations 1 + 11 -->\n- [x] No backfill of historical data (table starts empty) <!-- satisfied: migrations/008_user_transactions.sql contains only DDL, no INSERT/UPDATE -->\n\n### FR-2: Write Path ‚Äî Populate on Settlement\n\nThe settlement worker writes to `user_transactions` when a round settles.\nAll writes use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` on `(wallet, match_id, event)` for\nidempotency.\n\n**Coinflip** (commit-reveal, 1v1):\n- **Join ‚Äî creator**: Written when the create route inserts the round into DB\n  (creator wallet is known at create time).\n- **Join ‚Äî opponent**: Written when PDA watcher detects phase change to LOCKED\n  (opponent wallet readable from on-chain account).\n- **Win + Loss**: On `settle_confirmed` in `settle-tx.ts`, insert two rows.\n  `win.amount_lamports` = payout (after fees). `loss.amount_lamports` =\n  original wager.\n\n**Lord of the RNGs** (commit-reveal, multi-player):\n- **No join rows** ‚Äî the PDA watcher sees the round state change but not\n  individual entries. Join visibility is deferred.\n- **Win + Loss**: On `settle_confirmed` in `settle-tx.ts`, insert one `win`\n  row for the winner and one `loss` row per losing entry. Entries array is\n  available from on-chain round data at settlement time.\n\n**Close Call** (pari-mutuel):\n- **All rows at settlement**: When `settleRound()` in `closecall-clock.ts`\n  completes, write one `join` + one outcome (`win`/`loss`/`refund`) row per\n  entry. Entries are in the round's `green_entries`/`red_entries` JSONB.\n- **Refund rows**: Only Close Call has backend-processed refunds (one-sided\n  rounds, single player, equal price). Coinflip/Lord refunds are\n  permissionless on-chain timeout ‚Äî the backend doesn't process them.\n\n**Game name mapping**: DB stores `coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall`. API maps to\nfrontend `GameId`: `lord` ‚Üí `lord-of-rngs`, `closecall` ‚Üí `close-call`.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] Coinflip: creator join row written at create time <!-- satisfied: routes/create.ts:208-215 ‚Äî insertUserTransaction after round INSERT -->\n- [x] Coinflip: opponent join row written at PDA watcher lock detection <!-- satisfied: worker/pda-watcher.ts:120-132 ‚Äî fire-and-forget on PHASE_LOCKED -->\n- [x] Coinflip: win + loss rows written at settlement with correct amounts and tx_sig <!-- satisfied: worker/settle-tx.ts:304-323 ‚Äî Promise.all win(payoutAmount)+loss(entryAmount) with txSignature -->\n- [x] Lord: win row for winner + loss rows for all losers at settlement <!-- satisfied: worker/settle-tx.ts:518-543 ‚Äî win(payoutAmount) + loss per non-winner entry -->\n- [x] Close Call: join + outcome rows per entry at settlement <!-- satisfied: worker/closecall-clock.ts:489-538 ‚Äî iterates green/red entries, join+outcome per entry -->\n- [x] Close Call: refund rows written for refund outcomes <!-- satisfied: worker/closecall-clock.ts:508-509,523-524 ‚Äî isRefund check writes refund event -->\n- [x] `match_id` links back to the correct round in `rounds` or `closecall_rounds` <!-- satisfied: coinflip/lord use round.match_id‚Üírounds; closecall uses roundId‚Üíclosecall_rounds.round_id -->\n- [x] No duplicate rows for the same event (idempotent via ON CONFLICT) <!-- satisfied: UNIQUE(wallet,match_id,event) in migration:27-29; all paths use ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING -->\n\n### FR-3: API Endpoint ‚Äî Transaction History\n\n```\nGET /profile/transactions?cursor=<id>&limit=<n>&game=<filter>\n```\n\n- **Auth**: JWT required. Returns transactions only for the authenticated\n  wallet (from JWT `sub` claim). No wallet parameter in URL ‚Äî prevents\n  enumeration.\n- **Pagination**: Cursor-based using `id` (descending). Default limit 20,\n  max 50.\n- **Filtering**: Optional `game` query param (`coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall`).\n- **Response shape**:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"transactions\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": 123,","numLines":100,"startLine":60,"totalLines":684}}}
